---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Main from "../components/html-structure/Main.astro";
import HeroSecondary from "../components/hero-secondary.astro";
import { ComputerDesktopIcon, VideoCameraIcon, SparklesIcon } from '@heroicons/vue/20/solid'
---

<Layout title="Rent the Daysland Palace theatre">
  <HeroSecondary
    tagline="Rent the Palace theatre"
    title="Host Your Dream Event at Daysland Palace Theatre"
    content="Make your day special">
  </HeroSecondary>


  <div class="relative overflow-hidden py-24 sm:py-32">
    <div class="absolute -top-80 left-[max(6rem,33%)] -z-10 transform-gpu blur-3xl sm:left-1/2 md:top-20 lg:ml-20 xl:top-3 xl:ml-56" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="aspect-[801/1036] w-[50.0625rem] bg-gradient-to-tr from-[#ff80b5] to-[#9089fc] opacity-30" style="clip-path: polygon(63.1% 29.6%, 100% 17.2%, 76.7% 3.1%, 48.4% 0.1%, 44.6% 4.8%, 54.5% 25.4%, 59.8% 49.1%, 55.3% 57.9%, 44.5% 57.3%, 27.8% 48%, 35.1% 81.6%, 0% 97.8%, 39.3% 100%, 35.3% 81.5%, 97.2% 52.8%, 63.1% 29.6%)" />
    </div>
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl lg:mx-0">
        <!-- <p class="text-lg font-semibold leading-8 tracking-tight text-indigo-600">Host Your Dream Event at The Daysland Palace Theatre</p> -->
        <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">Creating Unforgettable Memories at a Historic Venue</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-xl leading-8 text-gray-700">Welcome to The Daysland Palace Theatre, a venue where your special events turn into enchanting experiences.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="mx-auto mt-16 grid max-w-2xl grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 gap-y-16 lg:mx-0 lg:mt-10 lg:max-w-none lg:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="relative lg:order-last lg:col-span-5">
          <svg class="absolute -top-[40rem] left-1 -z-10 h-[64rem] w-[175.5rem] -translate-x-1/2 stroke-gray-900/10 [mask-image:radial-gradient(64rem_64rem_at_111.5rem_0%,white,transparent)]" aria-hidden="true">
            <defs>
              <pattern id="e87443c8-56e4-4c20-9111-55b82fa704e3" width="200" height="200" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">
                <path d="M0.5 0V200M200 0.5L0 0.499983" />
              </pattern>
            </defs>
            <rect width="100%" height="100%" stroke-width="0" fill="url(#e87443c8-56e4-4c20-9111-55b82fa704e3)" />
          </svg>
          <figure class="border-l border-indigo-600 pl-8">
            <blockquote class="text-xl font-semibold leading-8 tracking-tight text-gray-900">
              <p>“Experience the magic of DaysArts and make your next event truly unforgettable by hosting it at the iconic Daysland Palace Theatre, where every occasion becomes a masterpiece of memories.”</p>
            </blockquote>
            <figcaption class="mt-8 flex gap-x-4">
              <div class="text-sm leading-6">
                <div class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Sharon and the DaysArts Team</div>
                <div class="text-gray-600"><a href="mailto:info@daysarts.ca" class="underline hover:no-underline" aria-label="Email us at info@daysarts.ca">info@daysarts.ca</a></div>
              </div>
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <div class="max-w-xl text-base leading-7 text-gray-700 lg:col-span-7">
          <p>Our historic theatre, with its dazzling marquee lights and classic Hollywood charm, offers a unique and glamorous setting for a variety of occasions. From dream weddings to dynamic community events, The Palace Theatre is more than just a location; it's a gateway to creating lasting memories.</p>
          <ul role="list" class="mt-8 max-w-xl space-y-8 text-gray-600">
            <li class="flex gap-x-3">
              <ComputerDesktopIcon class="mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-indigo-600" aria-hidden="true" />
              <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Epic Gaming Nights:</strong> Turn our theater into the ultimate gaming arena, where you can play your favorite video games on the big screen, complete with immersive sound.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-x-3">
              <VideoCameraIcon class="mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-indigo-600" aria-hidden="true" />
              <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Classic Movie Marathons:</strong> Host a movie marathon night, selecting films from a specific genre, era, or director, ideal for cinephiles or a unique gathering with friends.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex gap-x-3">
              <SparklesIcon class="mt-1 h-5 w-5 flex-none text-indigo-600" aria-hidden="true" />
              <span><strong class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Talent Showcases:</strong> Utilize the stage for an open mic night, local talent show, or comedy evening, offering a fantastic platform for artists and entertainers in the community.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="mt-16 text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900">A Wedding Venue Like No Other</h2>

          <p class="mt-6">Imagine your wedding day set against the backdrop of our illustrious theater, where every detail from the red carpet aisle to the star-studded decor is tailored to your vision. Exchange vows under the spotlight, creating a scene straight out of a romantic film, with your guests comfortably seated in plush theater seats. Opt for a 1940s Old Hollywood theme or personalize your day to reflect your favorite cinematic moments. With a venue fee of just $250.00, transform The Palace Theatre into your stage, making your wedding a splendid showcase of your love story.</p>
          <p class="mt-6">Ready to transform The Daysland Palace Theatre into your personal event space? For more information and to start planning your unforgettable event, contact Sharon at <a href="tel:+17803742403" class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-indigo-600" aria-label="Call us at 780-374-2403">780-374-2403</a> or
            <a href="mailto:info@daysarts.ca" class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-indigo-600" aria-label="Email us at info@daysarts.ca">info@daysarts.ca</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</Layout>